<br>
Don't believe the hype about necromancer/beastlord pets being almost as good as ours.  It's true at some levels though (the necromancer 49 pet is really almost as good as our 49 one).  Once you get above 51 though, our pets are really the only ones that get much better.  And the damage shield makes them like twice as powerful..really <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Here are some common things my necro friend and I do..  <br>
<br>
Fear kite in skyfire..boring, slow but steady experience, no risk of death....i pull the named cycle usually, we get lots of spells ( i give 'em away to people who need them hehe), i put up a water pet he puts up his rogue pet..two backstabbing pets RIP through any mob where you can fear kite!  <br>
<br>
Lower guk, this is really fun!  We plow through the dead side with our pets.  I dd, the necro heals and slows.<br>
<br>
Howling stones, just at the entrance, this is the place for experience!  We both use our pets, we break the spawns up and just pull away.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    The necromancer heals the pet usually once a fight, I dd if one of the pets is about to die.  <br>
<br>
Don't believe the crap people say about necromancer heals...the 54 necromancer heal takes 500-ish of their hitpoints, and heals players 500 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ...HOWEVER...due to the PVP damage reduction code, and the way these spells are coded....They heal MORE on your pet!!!  The 500 heal actually heals over 700 damage when casted on a pet (not going to get into a debate over this, i used to play a high level necro, and if you dont believe me, go try it)<br>
<br>
So yeah...mages are a class that goes really well with any of the classes that add some versatility to a group.  Necromancers add an INCREDIBLE amount of versatility (I would argue the most of any class in the game bar none).<br>
<br>
Sorry forgot one other awesome thing that magician/wizards and necros can do....say your all low on health, the necro can heal you all up...how?  Well, the necro goes into lich mode, you make an eye of zomm, and the necromancer can tap your eye of zomm back to heal him and his group even if you are too low on mana to pull mobs for him to tap...this can make recovery from a near-wipe-out much quicker..just a nice tip. <p>53 Magician-Unguilded-Firiona Vie-More active culture than a carton of Yoplait</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukathatlafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KathatlaFV</A> at: 6/24/02 9:17:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umethoshc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Methoshc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(6/25/02 1:42:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.wi.rr.com/loreleaf/pdf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magican good duo with wizard and necro?</span><hr size=1> mage/necro is a mean combination.  I've duo'd in akheva playing my mage to pull (higher level) and then the necro to snare/fear.  With a 59 mage and 55 necro, it's ungodly the speed at which the necro goes for the group.  So if you're looking further down the road, a wiz/mag/necro setup is going to be ungodly for you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
