<br>
This is not log parsed, or &quot;hard&quot; data.  This is simply my obsevations over several days from soloing and grouping with a lower level BL on Golra island.<br>
<br>
All four of my pets would get totally slapped around if they spent much time at all face to face.  This was not major, as I shocked three times when soloing... usually tanking after the second shock.   I only have the earth and the fire foci.<br>
<br>
The most common result was Me down one bubble health, 2 bubbles mana.  Fire and Earth pets between 20 and 40 health.  Unfocused Air or Water pets dead or nearly dead.<br>
<br>
Duoing with the BL, I would only Shock once (I always Malo'ed).  The Beast Lord cast no spells, had to save mana to rangerheal the pet.  I used the fire pet for duoing.  My pets were 29th circle, BL's pet is from what?  22nd circle?<br>
<br>
My pet doing all the damage (DW 24-28s) and cast firespell.  BL pet was hitting for like 16ish, and was not DW or DA, that I could tell.  It did proc a ice DD of some nature that was most often resisted.  For reasons I do not understand, the BL pet took all the damage... Fire pet had more than 90% health at end of each fight.  Maybe the MoB was attacking the lower level first.  In any case, the fights lasted longer than when I soloed (not as much nuking) and the lower level BL pet had sightly over 50% health nearly every time.  Where my pets got hit for up to 61, the BL pets never seemed to be hit for more than 40ish.<br>
<br>
Now, you can spout words about &quot;emotional data&quot; and &quot;objective testing&quot; and the like.  I agree with you, but I play to have fun, not as research.  If someone comes on here with all the &quot;hard&quot; data to prove otherwise, I have no problem admitting I was wrong.   I still feel that the BL is an inferior class, and I have no doubt that our pets would rip them to shreds, but, currently, my gut feeling is that BL pets would make a better &quot;tank&quot; if that is ALL that you are after.   <p>Moghedan Carns,<BR>
Gnome Summoner<BR>
